            "date": "2011-11-14 12:58:45", 
            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "With Kubuntu (Oneiric), if you right click a text file in the dolphin file browser and select \"Open With\"->\"gedit\", a new gedit window comes up with the selected file opened but also a second tab is created with \"untitled document\". ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "When closing the editor, gedit always asks if you want to save the redundant file - which is really annoying.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "Starting gedit from the command line or from Nautilus does not exhibit this problem.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
